@node Introduction "Introduction"
@{fg shine}
         Speech File Renumberer V3.00 - By: John White - Public Domain.
        ----------------------------------------------------------------

@{fg text}
 Speech File Renumberer V3.00 (SFR) is a small program that allows you to
 Decrease or Increase your `Speaking Words/Sentences to be Activated'
 (SWSTBA), within a certain range.

 Imagine you have completed SWSTBA from 1 to 900 but have since found out
 you have missed SWSTBA 600. Normally this would mean manually changing
 SWSTBA 600 to 900 into 601 to 901 so that you could make room for SWSTBA
 600. This scenario would not be nice to say the least. SFR was written to
 help with this problem. Please Note. At the moment SFR is very basic.

 SFR V3.00 needs at least Operating System 39 to work.
