@node Starting "Getting Started"

@{fg shine} From the Startup-Sequence@{fg text}

 Put SFR into the C drawer, of the floppy disk or hard drive you are going
 to boot with. To run SFR simply re-boot your amiga. If you try and boot
 from a floppy drive when you have an hard drive the hard drive will have
 priority over the floppy drive. If you only have floppy drives or only have
 a hard drive then SFR will boot as normal.

 @{" CLI Arguments " Link "Arguments"}

@{fg shine} From CLI@{fg text}

 Put SFR anywhere you please. In your C drawer, Tools drawer or where ever.
 Start a CLI Process (I.e use CLI, Shell or Workbench's `Execute' menu) and
 type the pathname for SFR (I.e WORK:Tools/SFR, SFR, etc) and then press
 ENTER. This will run SFR. Alternatively. Type the pathname for SFR followed
 by one or more CLI Arguments and then press ENTER.

 @{" CLI Arguments " Link "Arguments"}

@{fg shine} From Workbench@{fg text}

 Make sure there is a TOOL Icon on SFR and then double-click on SFR. This
 will run SFR, which will then read the TOOL Icon for SFR ToolTypes. If it
 finds any it will set the appropriate values inside SFR.

 @{" ToolTypes    " Link "ToolTypes"}
